        "subtitle": "Classic Damascus with Warm Rosewood",
        "intro_content": "<p>The <strong>Xinzuo B27 Yi Series</strong> pairs a <strong>10Cr15CoMoV steel core</strong> with 67 layers of Damascus cladding and beautiful <strong>rosewood handles</strong>, creating a knife that performs as well as it looks. At <strong>60 HRC</strong>, the 10Cr15CoMoV core — Xinzuo’s refined take on VG10-class steel — delivers excellent edge retention, corrosion resistance, and a balance of hardness and toughness that suits both precise slicing and everyday prep. Each blade is vacuum heat-treated and deep-frozen for optimal grain structure. With 10 knife types including paring, santoku, bunka, boning, cleaver, and bread knife, the Yi Series covers the full range of kitchen tasks. The warm rosewood handles give the Yi Series a timeless, traditional character that appeals to cooks who favour natural materials. A strong all-rounder in Xinzuo’s premium tier.</p>",
