        "heading": "What makes the Yi Series a great all-rounder",
        "content": "<p>The Yi Series uses <strong>10Cr15CoMoV steel</strong> — Xinzuo’s take on VG10-class performance. See how it compares in independent testing. <a href=\"/blogs/news/vg10-steel-vs-10cr15comov-guide\">VG10 vs 10Cr15CoMoV compared</a></p><p>Learn how 67-layer Damascus construction protects the cutting core while adding striking visual character to each blade. <a href=\"/blogs/news/damascus-pattern-performance-price-guide\">Damascus pattern guide</a></p><p>Understand how <strong>steel hardness</strong> at 60 HRC balances edge retention with ease of sharpening for everyday kitchen use. <a href=\"/blogs/news/knife-steel-hardness-guide\">Steel hardness guide</a></p><p>Keep your Yi Series Damascus blades looking and performing their best with proper maintenance techniques. <a href=\"/blogs/news/how-to-care-for-damascus-steel-knives\">Damascus knife care guide</a></p><p>Explore the different Japanese knife types available in the Yi Series and which suits your cooking style. <a href=\"/blogs/news/japanese-knife-types-explained\">Japanese knife types guide</a></p><p>Want the same 10Cr steel with ebony wood handles? The <strong>Ji Series</strong> uses proprietary 12Cr18MoV steel in a 67-layer Damascus build. <a href=\"/collections/x08-ji-series\">Shop the Ji Series</a></p>",
